.TH "IMAGEBUILDER-PUT-COMPONENT-POLICY" "a" "" ""
.SH NAME
imagebuilder-put-component-policy \- Applies a policy to a component
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
Applies a policy to a component. We recommend that you call the RAM API \fI\%CreateResourceShare\fP to share resources. If you call the Image Builder API \fBPutComponentPolicy\fP , you must also call the RAM API \fI\%PromoteResourceShareCreatedFromPolicy\fP in order for the resource to be visible to all principals with whom the resource is shared.
.sp
See also: AWS API Documentation
.sp
See \(aqaws help\(aq for descriptions of global parameters.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
  put\-component\-policy
\-\-component\-arn <value>
\-\-policy <value>
[\-\-cli\-input\-json | \-\-cli\-input\-yaml]
[\-\-generate\-cli\-skeleton <value>]
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH OPTIONS
.sp
\fB\-\-component\-arn\fP (string)
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the component that this policy should be applied to.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB\-\-policy\fP (string)
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The policy to apply.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB\-\-cli\-input\-json\fP | \fB\-\-cli\-input\-yaml\fP (string)
Reads arguments from the JSON string provided. The JSON string follows the format provided by \fB\-\-generate\-cli\-skeleton\fP\&. If other arguments are provided on the command line, those values will override the JSON\-provided values. It is not possible to pass arbitrary binary values using a JSON\-provided value as the string will be taken literally. This may not be specified along with \fB\-\-cli\-input\-yaml\fP\&.
.sp
\fB\-\-generate\-cli\-skeleton\fP (string)
Prints a JSON skeleton to standard output without sending an API request. If provided with no value or the value \fBinput\fP, prints a sample input JSON that can be used as an argument for \fB\-\-cli\-input\-json\fP\&. Similarly, if provided \fByaml\-input\fP it will print a sample input YAML that can be used with \fB\-\-cli\-input\-yaml\fP\&. If provided with the value \fBoutput\fP, it validates the command inputs and returns a sample output JSON for that command.
.sp
See \(aqaws help\(aq for descriptions of global parameters.
.SH EXAMPLES
.sp
\fBTo apply a resource policy to a component\fP
.sp
The following \fBput\-component\-policy\fP command applies a resource policy to a build component to enable cross\-account sharing of build components. We recommend you use the RAM CLI command create\-resource\-share. If you use the EC2 Image Builder CLI command put\-component\-policy, you must also use the RAM CLI command promote\-resource\-share\-create\-from\-policy in order for the resource to be visible to all principals with whom the resource is shared.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
aws imagebuilder put\-component\-policy \e
    \-\-image\-arn arn:aws:imagebuilder:us\-west\-2:123456789012:component/examplecomponent/2019.12.02/1 \e
    \-\-policy \(aq{ "Version": "2012\-10\-17", "Statement": [ { "Effect": "Allow", "Principal": { "AWS": [ "123456789012" ] }, "Action": [ "imagebuilder:GetComponent", "imagebuilder:ListComponents" ], "Resource": [ "arn:aws:imagebuilder:us\-west\-2:123456789012:component/examplecomponent/2019.12.02/1" ] } ] }\(aq
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
